## Issue Inventory and Initial Analysis

### ISSUE-01 — Date-dependent tab counts must use fixed EST, not UTC or daylight-saving EDT

Original report:
> In restock management tabs, the counts on the tabs that depend on dates seem to be using UTC. They should actually use EST fixed (no daylight savings, no EDT). This might have already been done; verify if it is already implemented, if so then skip this and indicate same.

Initial code findings:
- `lib/restock-number.ts` uses `Intl.DateTimeFormat(... timeZone: 'America/New_York')`, which is Eastern time but observes daylight saving time. This is not fixed EST.
- `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx` formats date-only strings via `new Date(`${value}T00:00:00`).toLocaleDateString()`, which depends on the runtime/browser local timezone.
- Upcoming Scheduled Re-orders count compares date-only strings (`po.reorder_date === item.next_reorder_date`) and therefore may not itself shift by timezone if both values are normalized as `YYYY-MM-DD`, but all date-derived display/helpers and any generated current-date defaults need a fixed-EST audit before claiming this issue is already resolved.

Status: planned; do not skip yet. Verification must prove fixed-EST behavior at date boundaries and during daylight-saving months.

### ISSUE-02 — Edit Request Items modal layers under other modals

Original report:
> When editing current restock requests, the edit request items modal opens with the wrong z index. It should be on top of all the other modals, but it ends up being at the very base/bottom in the z index.

Initial code findings:
- Restock modals generally use `fixed inset-0 z-50`.
- The edit request flow is launched from the request details modal and therefore needs a stacked modal layer above the request details layer, not the same or lower z-index.
- Resolution should define explicit modal z-index tiers for base modal vs nested edit modal rather than relying on render order.

Status: planned.

### ISSUE-03 — PO notes are missing wherever PO details are shown

Original report:
> PO's aren't displaying the PO notes anywhere where PO details are shown.

Initial code findings:
- The selected PO detail modal currently displays `selectedPurchaseOrder.notes` as a PO Notes callout.
- The print/PDF document flows and PO list/group detail surfaces must be audited because the issue says "anywhere where PO details are shown," not only the selected PO modal.
- Resolution should make PO notes visible in every PO detail surface, including selected PO modal, supplier PO list cards/details, print output, and PDF output.

Status: partially present; planned audit and completion.

### ISSUE-04 — Edit Request Items button width should fit text

Original report:
> The 'edit request items' button is too wide, the width needs to fit to text and not span to section nor flex.

Initial code findings:
- The selected request detail modal renders the button with `w-full`, causing it to span the full section width.
- Resolution is likely a small UI class change to inline-flex / fit-content sizing.

Status: planned.

### ISSUE-05 — PO PDF download must support multi-page PDFs

Original report:
> The PO pdf download feature only generates a single page PDF. It needs to support multi page pdf generation for POs that are longer than one page. Currently it adds a note at end of the single page to indicate use the print feature instead; that isn't the behaviour we want.

Initial code findings:
- `handleDownloadPurchaseOrderPdf` caps output at 44 visible lines and appends a "Use Print" truncation note.
- The PDF object tree currently creates exactly one page (`/Count 1` with a single page object).
- Resolution must remove truncation and generate as many PDF pages as needed for all PO lines and notes.

Status: planned.

