## Phase 3 — PO Notes Everywhere PO Details Are Shown

Phase status: completed 2026-06-20.

### Scope
- ISSUE-03.

### Implementation tasks
1. Inventory every PO details surface in restock workflow code:
   - selected PO modal,
   - supplier PO group/list rows,
   - print output,
   - PDF output,
   - edit/place/receive PO surfaces when they show PO details.
2. Ensure PO notes render consistently when present and are omitted cleanly when blank.
3. Include PO notes in generated print HTML.
4. Include PO notes in generated PDF content, including multi-page continuation from Phase 4 if implemented in the same pass or after Phase 4 if sequencing demands.

### Single-pass exit criteria
- Any user-facing PO detail view/output includes PO notes if the PO has notes.
- No blank "PO Notes" label appears for POs without notes.

### Truthful verification after completion
- Structural check for `purchaseOrder.notes` / `selectedPurchaseOrder.notes` usage in all PO details/output paths.
- Manual UI smoke with one PO that has notes:
  1. View the PO in the PO tab/list/detail modal.
  2. Open print preview.
  3. Download PDF.
  4. Confirm notes are visible in all three places.

### Completion log
- Completed in `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx`.
- Kept existing selected PO modal notes display and added PO notes to supplier PO list cards.
- Added PO notes to print HTML and PDF content generation so exported PO detail outputs include the same notes.
- Added notes to PO search matching to make noted POs discoverable from the PO tab search.
- Verification performed: `rg -n "PO Notes:|purchaseOrder.notes|po.notes|selectedPurchaseOrder.notes" components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx` confirmed notes appear in UI, print, PDF, and search paths. Manual browser smoke is still recommended with a PO that has notes.

---

## Phase 4 — Multi-page PO PDF Generation

Phase status: completed 2026-06-20.

### Scope
- ISSUE-05.

### Implementation tasks
1. Replace the current single-page/capped PDF generator with a multi-page generator.
2. Remove the truncation line that tells users to use print for the full layout.
3. Paginate PO content across pages based on line height and page margins.
4. Generate a valid PDF page tree with one page object per page and all page content streams referenced correctly.
5. Include PO notes, supplier/status/date metadata, all line items, totals, and page numbers.
6. Keep the print handler separate from the PDF handler.

### Single-pass exit criteria
- A PO with more lines than one page downloads as a valid multi-page PDF.
- No PO item lines are omitted.
- No "Use Print" truncation message remains.

### Truthful verification after completion
- Programmatic structural checks:
  - no `maxVisibleLines` cap remains in the PDF handler,
  - PDF `/Count` reflects generated page count,
  - handler constructs multiple page objects when content exceeds one page.
- Manual UI smoke:
  1. Use or seed a PO with enough items to exceed one page.
  2. Click **Download as PDF**.
  3. Open the PDF and confirm multiple pages, all items, notes, total, and page numbers are present.

### Completion log
- Completed in `components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx`.
- Removed the single-page `maxVisibleLines`/`Use Print` truncation path.
- Added line wrapping, per-page slicing, dynamic `/Pages /Kids` generation, dynamic `/Count ${pages.length}`, individual page/content objects, and page numbers.
- Included PO notes and every PO line in the downloadable PDF content source before pagination.
- Verification performed: `! rg -n "maxVisibleLines|Use Print for full layout|/Count 1" components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx` confirmed the old cap/truncation/single-page count are gone; `rg -n "wrapPdfLine|/Count \${pages.length\}|Page \${pageIndex \+ 1} of \${pages.length}" components/admin/restock/restock-workflow-tabs.tsx` confirmed the new pagination structure. Manual PDF-open smoke is still recommended with a long PO.

